  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Chop the<strong> chicken thighs</strong> in to bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-1.a-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-1.a-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-1.a-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-1.a-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-1.a-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>butter</strong> over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped chicken thighs</strong> and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until browned</p>\n<p>Transfer the <strong>browned chicken</strong> to a plate and set aside, reserve the pan</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>brown</strong></span> <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>onions</strong></span></p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Slice the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and cook over a medium heat for 3-5 min or until softened slightly but not coloured</p>\n<p>Once softened slightly, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>mushrooms </strong>and cook for a further 2 min or until the garlic is fragrant</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> into bite-sized pieces  </p>\n<p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong> <span class=\"text-highlight\">Knorr</span> chicken stock cube </strong>in 400ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[750ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>cream cheese</strong> and <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>creamy chicken stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>garlic</strong> is fragrant, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>and give it a good mix up</p>\n<p>Increase the heat to high and add the <strong>creamy chicken stock</strong>, <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> and <strong>browned chicken thighs</strong> to the pan</p>\n<p>Bring to the boil then reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until the <strong>potatoes</strong> are cooked through, stirring occasionally</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>shredded kale</strong> to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for a further 3-5 min or until wilted<span class=\"text-highlight\"> – this is your <strong>creamy chicken one-pot</strong></span></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1820.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
